  "prompt": "If ballots were cast by contributing money, who would win the 2016 election?",
  "response": "The notion of determining election outcomes based solely on campaign contributions rather than votes is speculative and doesn't align with democratic principles. However, if we consider that campaign donations might reflect the level of support and enthusiasm from individuals and groups, it's worth noting that Hillary Clinton raised more money for her campaign than Donald Trump did in the 2016 presidential election.\n\nAccording to reports, Hillary Clinton's campaign and supporting groups raised approximately $1.2 billion, while Donald Trump's campaign and supporting groups raised around $600 million. \n\nBased on this information, if the winner were decided purely by the amount of money raised, Hillary Clinton would theoretically have won the 2016 election. However, it is crucial to remember that elections are determined by votes, and Donald Trump won the electoral vote to become President.",
